"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-05-paris-2024-olympics-oborodudu-zooms-into-semi-final-in-womens-wrestling\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's Blessing Oborududu has qualified for the semi-final of women's Wrestling 68kg at the 2024 Olympic Games.  Oborududu defeated her French opponent, Koumba Larroque 6-2 in their quarter-final match.  She is now guaranteed to leave Paris 2024 with a medal by qualifying for the last four.  Earlier, the African champion defeated her Canadian opponent Linda Morais in the quarter-finals.  The powerful wrestler had a slow start conceding two points but she rallied in the second half, to score six consecutive points, going on to win the match 8-2 on points.  Oborodudu will be in action again later this evening.  Transfer: De Gea set to join new club after Genoa's move collapsed  Rivers United confirms participation in Bayelsa's pre-season tournament  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"